sn't it?) and I don't<br />&gt; have a POSIX.4 copy at hand. <br /><br />It's defined by "DEF_PRIORITY" in ticks, currently<br /><br />  #define DEF_PRIORITY	(20*HZ/100)	/* 200 ms time slice */<br /><br />so the correct value would probably be<br /><br />	t.tv_nsec = DEF_PRIORITY*1000000/HZ;<br /><br />but that's just the system "default" value, and I suspect that the<br />function should return the per-process thing which is more like<br /><br />	t.tv_sec = current-&gt;priority * 1000000/HZ;<br /><br />could you test it out and see if it works for you?<br /><br />I don't want to change any of the RT stuff as I don't have any<br />test-programs that care about it, and as such I don't have any personal<br />interest.. <br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
